\f0\b Coding Guidelines\
  editing\

\f1\b0     editor uses tabs\
    tab width 4\
    indent width 4\
    wrap lines\
    indent wrapped lines by 6\

\f0\b   classes/objects\

\f1\b0     constants set off with a k, kConstantString, kPDefaultZone\
    static set off with an s, sClassVariable\
    outlets set off with an o, oTextField\
    instance variables set off with my, myInstanceVariable (rather than using m (confusing) or _ (verboten))\
    keys in dictionaries are generally lowerCaseInterCaps to mirror key value coding\
    arrays are designated with pluralized nouns, e.g. items instead of itemArray\
    header imports generally follow the pattern:\
      #import "MyClass.h"\
      #import "ProjectClass(es).h"\
      #import <FrameworkClass(es).h>\
  \

